caption: Had a delicious ahi (rare) and my fiance had a blackened ahi (medium) they were incredible definitely would recommend this place!
The fish tacos were the star, very hearty. Grilled snapper on the dry side. Salad greens fresh. Large portions. Call ahead for take out during peak hours because that line goes out the door.
Great food!

Our snapper was delicious! Even the sides were on point. It just took awhile in line and waiting at the table. We ended ordering online, exploring the market nearby, and returning when the food was ready. We would definitely order it again!
Love it!!!! Service was great and staff was awesome. The food was fantastic. Definitely a place to stop by and eat in or to go.
The mahi sandwich was better then the mahi plate but at half the cost
Mahi burger was pretty good. Fish was a bit dry but I guess that’s the nature of completely cooked fish.

You will need to wait in line to place your order. They will give you a number and bring your meal to your table. Inside or outside dining experiance. Food was got and delicious.
Excellent good at a good price. The $6 Maitai happy hour is the best! Get the ono, great fish and tastes great with the cajun seasoning.
Charbroil Mahi mahi perfectly cooked!

Absolutely a must place to eat! If you want good, fresh fish at a decent price, eat here! I had the garden salad with blackened Mahi and my friend had the blackened snapper meal. Get the sesame and/or the Papaya Seed dressing!
Omg... great great food!!!

Great fish plates at a reasonable price. The fish is super fresh, seasoned well and cooked to perfection... moist tasty and not dry. I really liked their butter sautéed version of the fish the best... what can go wrong with a like butter haha. Blackened Mahi Mahi was a little bitter for my taste. Must visit restaurant if you are visiting Hawaii.

A great find!  Excellent fresh fish and reasonable prices.  Don't miss the fried calamari.  Over the top friendly service. Elevator access is available but a little hard to find. Just ask inside and they will direct you.
Simply fantastic. Best fish in town.
The grilled snapper was done perfectly and the cajun rice was very good.
OMG Amazing!  Had the grilled Mahi Mahi and they had a low carb option of a caesar salad.  So moist and perfectly cooked👍 I ate half of it before taking the picture it was so tasty😊

I would highly recommend to use their app  to order for a pick up.   That makes it much easier.  They do get SUPER busy nowadays. The first time, it was great - fast and yummy. The 2nd time, they were slow (because they were busy) our order was not ready till 20 min after the scheduled pick up time - and some fish didn’t have much flavors.  Many #glutenfree options here.   Generous portion.  If you need to keep the safety distance while you wait or eat, make sure to avoid the peak time.   The staff is doing their best but there were clueless space invader patrons there when I went to pick up around 7:30 on Friday.  #covidtime

Amazing! I don’t eat a lot of fish, but wanted to try something authentic or seafood-ish. I ordered Mahi Mahi plate and it tastes excellent and very fresh! My husband ordered the fish tacos which was above average. Also we ordered the deep fried calamari which is superb! Drinks are also very good especially during their legit (low price) happy hour. One of our drinks was late because they were busy, but they made up for that!

Always good for a fish dinner. Sautéed Mahi Mahi when in season..( winter time ) April through July is ONO season.. Summer time is AHI (yellow fin tuna). When in season,  locally caught, so it is fresh.. From my experience.
I loved the blackened salmon with Cajun rice. Rice isn’t very spicy but flavorful. Service was quick. Quantity and quality of food both are really good.
Super delicious and worth the line. So glad to see this Maui fave make it over here. Happy hour is great, too! I love the fresh catch plate and the fish burger!!
Very enjoyable and fresh.

This is a great place for dinner especially if you are on a budget. The food is very tasty and fish and chicken are available. You can sit outside if you wish and watch the passers by. Close to most major hotels and International Market Mall. Recommended.
Perfectly cooked fish..We ordered a grilled Mahi mahi and blackened Ahi fresh fish plates. Both were yummmm😋😋😋
The shrimp tacos were amazing!
So delicious! Honestly wasn't expecting much but the food was super tasty. Really friendly and hardworking staff. If there's a line, worth it.
Loco moco is definitely a hit!
Hands down the best fish I've had in my life. I got the ahi cajun dish and it was so to die for. Worth the wait. Good portions.

The Seafood Pasta was DELICIOUS!!  I highly recommend this restaurant for a nice dinner!  Several options, many different types of fish to choose from. They have a taco and beer daily for $7.  And happy hour from 3-6.  The fries were really good.  Good prices on kids plates.  We will definitely be going back.
Amazing dinner!!! I had fish tacos and my husband had blackened Ono.  The home potatoes were so delicious and the cole slaw was great too.  Highly recommend if your in Oahu!!!!
Food was excellent and the service was great! I ate until I was full, and wanted to continue eating more. Will definitely return before the end of our trip!
Absolutely amazing fish
Super!
The seafood pasta was great. Can’t wait to go back!

Stopped by this restaurant, with the assumption it was good because of the long line outside, very hungry with my large family. What a disappointment! All the food was bland, with over cooked chicken and hard rice. Nobody was satisfied with their meal. The prices were a bit expensive for what you got, with it being $10 for one margarita (that wasn’t even all the way up the glass, about 2/3 full). I ordered the fish tacos with french fries and coleslaw. The fries were very good, the coleslaw not so much. It was made with the same tartar sauce served with the fish tacos, and quite watery, tasting like vinegar and pickles mostly. The fish tacos were quite tasteless, prompting me to only eat because I was hungry. Lesson learned to never go here again.
Best grilled fish in Honolulu at decent prices.
The Mahi Mahi is the bomb here. Very tasty and lite. Rice was exceptional also.  Little spendy but good.
This place suprised me. The food is awsome.
While competing with sit down restaurant prices, this market provided us with our favorite fish dinners out of our entire combined six week stay.
The best FISH I’ve ever tasted 🤤🤤🤤🤤🔥🔥🔥🔥
Delicious food! Best fish tacos! Great happy hour drinks. Amazing onion rings! Friendly staff. Clean. Plenty of tables inside and a few outside. Went twice in five days! Highly recommend.

This we some of the freshest fish I’ve ever had! The service was excellent as well, the staff had excellent menu knowledge and were so kind! This was the best place I’ve ate at in Waikiki. The flavors were excellent and the fish was cooked to perfection. Worth every dollar! They also have beer and taco specials and a happy hour! I highly recommend!
The service was absolutely amazing, wasn’t a huge fan of the fish tacos. Next time I’ll try chicken. But everything was amazing.
Not a fan of the food at all. Got the cajun style mahi mahi with home fries. Wouldn't go back.
Amazing food and got our food really fast after we ordered... Did have to wait a bit in line to order. Worth the wait for suurreee
Fish was great!
The food was amazing!!

This place has amazing food. The kids menu provides a fairly large portion, at least the quesadilla and pasta options. Note if your kid is a picky eater the quesadilla includes refried beans and salsa, you can also add protein if you want more than just cheese. The only thing I wasn't overly enthused with was the blackened sashimi, but it was still good.
So good that we ate here 3 times while on vacation for a week. The fish options were awesome and reasonably priced for everything you got. I would highly recommend!
You know there's nothing like the original in Maui but this place is damn close the food is fabulous.

Excellent fresh catch, cooked to your liking ...I got mine Ahi Blackened with Cajun Rice on the side and some local brews on draft. I got Maui Brewings Big Swell. The wife got a burger (so there is something for everyone). It seemed like a blended burger , beef lamb and sausage. Delicious!
Very good. I had the dinner blackened shrimp tacos with rice and potatoes. There servings are much more than one person can eat.
The food is pretty good, if a little pricey. I would really love to see more of traditional hawaiian preparation of fish as well.

I always ask for recommendations from the people who live in the area when I travel and this place was recommended to me by one of the front desk team members at Hyatt Centric. I ordered Ahi Tuna with calamari from Paia through Uber Eats right before they closed and was not disappointed 👍 You could tell that the seafood is so fresh and cooked with care, owners and staff take pride in their work. The main course options are slightly expensive but if you are in the area I would recommend to try Paia at least once.
Delicious and efficient
All the servers were very nice and the portions were huge. I could not even finish it!
Meals are okay but...over 25% discount  for locals!? This is discrimination.Avoid this place if you are tourist.

My husband and I came here for dinner and we were pleasantly blown away by how delicious our food was. The margaritas on the happy hour menu did not disappoint in taste or alcohol 😉, food was fresh hot and delicious and the staff were super friendly! Definitely ONO!
Fish burger was a perfect fish sandwich. Was excellent and will definitely be coming here again!
I usually take out from here - great food and delicious preparation!
Delishish fish fare at very reasonable prices!
Great food, good service, local produce. What is not to like!

My family and I were living in a hotel for an extended period when we moved to the island and Paia was right down the street. It's surprisingly hard to find quality, affordable cooked fish in Waikiki. Paia is it and they nail it every time. The Ono is cooked to perfection and whether you decide to get the burger or the plated fish, both are sure to please. We usually got burgers because the coleslaw is also really good. I also tried the seafood pasta and the sauce was delicious and they did not skimp on the fish.  Additionally, the staff is really nice and accommodating. My five year old just wanted fish with no sides so we ordered him an Ono burger with no bun or toppings and they were happy to oblige every time. While we're happy to be in our house, we miss being walking distance to Paia and can't wait to visit again!
Always fantastic and delicious.  Great service.  Delicious fresh food! 🦐🦞🦀🦑🦪

We got the seafood pasta & it was very good! There was a  misunderstanding while ordering online which caused our order to be incorrect, but the mgr ( so wish I would’ve gotten his name) went above and beyond to correct the issue & for that alone its 10 stars! Thank you!
My husband and I came here and LOVED our fish! Perfectly cooked at a great price! Mahalo!

Very friendly, even better food. I was very pleased! The grilled Ono with home fries was very well done. The Mahi was superbly done, with the rice and home fries. The fried shrimp was okay, nothing special. Their tartar sauce was a pleasant surprise, with a him of sweetness. I will be going back.
Great fish sandwich

Super fresh fish, very well cooked, great sides and friendly staff. I would eat here everyday!

Now, I work on a Kalakaua just a block away from the restaurant I ho at least 3 times a week during my lunch break, I absolutely love this place, it's clean an pretty well organized, staff is absolutely amazing, polite, competent  and really customers oriented, always ready to reccomend something good based on my tastes and not on what they need to sell that day. Friendly. Fast. Quality. If you are visiting Hawaii and are looking for seafood then this should be your first stop. For half the cost of other sea food in Waikiki it knocks it out of the park. I suggest the catch of the day sauteed.

Paia Fish Market is Excellent!!! From the friendly staff, the clean restaurant, generous  portions and the extremely delicious food,  My sister and I could NOT ask for any thing MORE!!! I will definitely return!!

My sister and I stopped here for lunch and honestly, the fried shrimp we ordered as an appetizer were the best I've ever had.  My meal consisted of grilled snapper and a huge organic salad. Everything was so fresh and delicious. I highly suggest eating at Paia if ever in Honolulu.

This is probably the best cost/taste ratio restaurant in waikiki. $10-$15 gets you enough tasty food to last 2 meals. Friendly staff, good seafood, nice location. Counter order, with staff bringing the food to your table. Local beer on tap and mixed drinks available. Recommended for a high quality, convenient, quick meal.

Pa'i'a is originally from Maui. And I must say that the new location here in Waikiki is just as good as the original!  They have a good food selection as well as beer on tap. You order at the counter and can get togo or dine in.  I will definitely be back here to try more items!

The Ahi was $27, but it was a large piece of Ahi and it came with potatoes, Cajun rice and coleslaw. It was a lot of food. Overall I would highly recommend and we will definitely be back.

PAIA FISH MARKET IS LEGIT!!!!!!! I started with the deep fried calamari and that alone was great. I followed next with the seafood pasta. Both dishes were made very well. The calamari was fried to perfection..and get this...not to chewy..I'm impressed The seafood pasta is heaven...seafood over linguine pasta sauteed with fresh basil, cream,  parmesan cheese, and it all comes together to knock your socks off. THIS PLACE IS AWESOME!!!

Best food in Waikiki. Incredible fish preparation. Amazing food and value compared to anything on Oahu. Mahi, ono, snapper, sashimi and salmon are consistently cooked to perfection. Kids menu is great and much appreciated. Salads are huge for the price! I’ve been eating here since they opened and this review is Long overdue. I’ve also eaten at the maui location many times and can say the same about it. Thank you Paia Fish Market!!!
Good food, try their clam cowder and blonde ale on tap. You can dine in and parking on the street was $3 an hour.

Fantastic and fresh fish. I ordered the ono burger, and it was one of the best sandwiches that I've ever had. The sandwich and fries were also one of the better meal deals in the city--extremely surprising for something so quality to be so reasonably priced and still a very large portion.
